HEADWORD: Raveling
<hw>Rav"el*ing</hw> <pr>(r⟦acr⟧v"'l*⟦icr⟧ng)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Also <ets>ravelling</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of
untwisting or of disentangling.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is raveled out; esp., a thread detached
from a texture.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Raven</ent>⟦br⟧
